article.headline: UNLV 78, Houston 62
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Wink Adams' 17 points led four UNLV players in double digits as the Runnin' Rebels beat Houston 78-62 on Saturday night. The Runnin' Rebels (13-2) never trailed after taking an early 12-11 lead and built as much as a 22-point advantage in the second half. UNLV won its ninth straight. Houston was plagued by poor shooting. The Cougars made just 3-of-24 attempts from 3-point range and 9-of-33 overall from the field in the opening half. For the game, Houston (5-6) sank just 5 of 36 3-pointers. Wendell White added 14 points for the Rebels while Gaston Essengue scored 11. Oliver Lafayette led Houston with 16 points, and Dion Dowell added 14. The Rebels built a 34-26 halftime lead.
